import json
import re
from datetime import datetime

def normalize_profile(profile):
    """Normalizes a professional profile according to the guidelines."""

    normalization_notes = []
    normalized_profile = profile.copy()

    # 1. Company Names
    def normalize_company_name(company_name):
        if not company_name:
            return company_name

        company_name = " ".join(company_name.split())  # Remove duplicate spaces
        company_name = re.sub(r'\.+', '.', company_name)  # Standardize periods
        company_name = company_name.replace('â€™', "'")  # Standardize apostrophes

        if company_name.upper() == company_name and len(company_name.split()) == 1:
            # Preserve all-caps for single-word acronyms/initialisms
            normalized_name = company_name
        else:
            normalized_name = ' '.join([word.capitalize() if word.lower() != 'inc' else 'Inc' for word in company_name.split()])

        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Inc.", "Inc")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Corp.", "Corp")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Llc.", "LLC")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("L.l.c.", "LLC")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("L. L. C.", "LLC")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("L. L. C", "LLC")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Llc", "LLC")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Limited", "Ltd.")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Self Employed", "Self-Employed")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Self employed", "Self-Employed")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Self-employed", "Self-Employed")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Fleishmanhillard", "Fleishman-Hillard")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Acme corp", "ACME Corp.")
        normalized_name = normalized_name.replace("Acme corp.", "ACME Corp.")
        return normalized_name
